I just found that 4 inquiries were killed in my spam bucket - sorry about that, no way I can retrieve the messages.  I have added armslist to my safe list as of 7/4/2014.

Including Ammo & Caps, but the longer it takes to sell, the fewer rounds will be left.
I started with 1000 rounds, and estimate you will get at least the 500 rounds shown, which is a good supply.  I'll throw in a bit of my awesome homemade black powder, so you can shoot right away.  You can buy 1 LB of Pyrodex at Walmart for $19, good for 2800 rounds (or 1750 magnum rounds), or get 777 if you want a higher muzzle velocity. The original instructions from freedom arms allowed for 1 grain of Bullseye pistol powder, but North American removed this high energy option from the instructions when they took over.  http://www.freedomarms.com/MiniRev.pdf

You will price compare, as you can buy these new.  I am giving you a chance to buy $400+ worth for $300 firm.  This is the magnum version (aka Super C&B), with many extras.  You may be able to buy just the pistol for $300 if you shop around.

You get:
1) Complete magnum pistol, stainless steel, used for hundreds of rounds.
2) Leather Holster, never used
3) Leather ammo sack, never used
4) Extra stainless cylinder; you can shoot 5, then quick change another 5, never used
5) Extra cylinder pin, never used - but they can wear out
6) Original case lock with keys
7) Pistol Case, padded
8) 500 Rounds of Ammo shown, 250x2, ++ whatever I have not shot yet...
9) Extra Nipples, 5, never used, easily replaceable wear part.
10) Extra Walnut grips, new, never used
11) 2 yellow powder scoops, standard and magnum load
12) Bullet seat crimp tool
13) Allen wrench for nipples and Hatpin perfect for clearing nipples
14) At least 500 CCI #11 primer caps+
15) Original instructions
16) NAA No hassle lifetime warranty, Just register, http://northamericanarms.com/warranty

I am NOT a motivated seller, this pistol is a blast. When is sells, I am using the $300 to buy another NAA pistol.  I originally purchased because I cannot find 22 LR ammo for my pistol.  Ammo for this C&B is readily available from NAA, inexpensively, but it may be quite a while before you burn through the ammo included.  There are some great alternate options to the NAA 30 grain bullets.  You can shoot 22 caliber pellets, high velocity, but lower energy overall.  For short range, you can get a sack of #4 buckshot, 21 grain balls, great snug fit.  You can use 6mm airsoft BBs! Indoors, using no powder, just the #11 primer, these are perfect parlor rounds, about 200-300 fps, just like an airsoft pistol, with a bang.
